---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Cookie Policy — AdWhisper"
  description="Cookie Policy for AdWhisper. Learn about the cookies we use, including advertising cookies from Ezoic and browser caching for the AI model."
  canonicalUrl="/cookie-policy"
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="prose animate-fade-in">
        <h1>Cookie Policy</h1>
        <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> March 10, 2026</p>

        <h2>What Are Cookies?</h2>
        <p>
          Cookies are small text files stored on your device when you visit a website. They serve various
          purposes including remembering your preferences, analyzing site usage, and enabling advertising.
        </p>

        <h2>Cookies We Use</h2>

        <h3>Essential Cookies</h3>
        <p>
          These cookies are necessary for the website to function properly. They do not collect
          personal information and cannot be disabled.
        </p>

        <h3>AI Model Cache</h3>
        <p>
          The Whisper AI model is stored in your browser using the Cache API and IndexedDB.
          While technically not cookies, this local storage serves a similar purpose — it allows
          the model to load quickly on return visits without re-downloading. This data:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Contains only AI model files (neural network weights)</li>
          <li>Does not contain any personal data</li>
          <li>Can be cleared through your browser's "Clear site data" settings</li>
          <li>Is approximately 150 MB in size</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Advertising Cookies (Ezoic)</h3>
        <p>
          We use Ezoic to serve advertisements. Ezoic and its partners may use cookies to:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Serve ads based on your interests and browsing behavior</li>
          <li>Limit the number of times you see an ad</li>
          <li>Measure the effectiveness of advertising campaigns</li>
          <li>Understand how visitors interact with advertisements</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          You can manage your advertising preferences through:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Your browser's cookie settings</li>
          <li><a href="https://www.youronlinechoices.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Your Online Choices</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://optout.networkadvertising.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Network Advertising Initiative Opt-Out</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://optout.aboutads.info/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Digital Advertising Alliance Opt-Out</a></li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Analytics Cookies</h3>
        <p>
          We may use analytics cookies to understand how visitors use our site. These cookies
          collect aggregated, anonymous information such as:
          page views, session duration, and general geographic location (country level).
        </p>

        <h2>Managing Cookies</h2>
        <p>
          Most web browsers allow you to control cookies through their settings. You can:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Block all cookies</li>
          <li>Accept only first-party cookies</li>
          <li>Delete cookies when you close your browser</li>
          <li>Clear all stored site data (including the AI model cache)</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Note that blocking essential cookies may affect the website's functionality, and
          clearing site data will require re-downloading the AI model on your next visit.
        </p>

        <h2>Updates</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Cookie Policy from time to time. Changes will be posted on this page.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
          For questions about our cookie practices, contact us at <strong>privacy@adwhisper.com</strong>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
